{"title":"fix(remediation): increase mem-load memory limit to prevent OOMKilled","body":"Root cause: The mem-load container memory limit (32Mi) is insufficient for the stress command (--vm-bytes 50M), causing OOMKilled when the container attempts to allocate more memory than allowed.

Evidence: Container mem-load runs command: stress --vm 1 --vm-bytes 50M --vm-keep with resources.limits.memory: 32Mi

Fix: Increase mem-load container memory limit from 32Mi to 64Mi."}
